question: 2 and 18 for the ship meme :D
answer:
I answered both of these before, but here you are, still :*

(2. Who is the most insecure and what makes them feel better?

- Crowley. Sure, Aziraphale might be an anxious mess at times, but Crowley has over six thousand years of hell and answering to hell to make him a mess at times, because even though technically, he knew which side he was supposed to be on, he hated it. Not that heaven would have been any better to him. He’s just really lost sometimes and being held helps a lot. Aziraphale is a steadying presence, warm and solid, but soft and Crowley just melts against him and buries his nose in his collar and takes a deep breath, because the angel smells like home and with him, Crowley never doubts his place.

18. When they fight, how do they make up?

They don’t fight often, but it does happen occasionally (on average every 43 months). Little disagreements happen more often, and it’s mostly little touches and an apologetic look, paired with “I’m sorry.” When it is something bigger, it takes a proper apology. And they’re both quite good at knowing if the other means it, by now.)

tags: idek what I'm writing anymore jfdhdjdksl
answer:
I answered 4. and 12. before, but i put them here again anyway.

(4. Who can’t keep their hands to themselves?

- Aziraphale. Once they get over themselves and the barriers they have internalised over six thousand years, and once they get closer, physically, Aziraphale is the one who learns to appreciate this side of human indulgence just as immensely as sushi, for example. He doesn’t Have to hold back anymore, so he won’t.

12. What first changes when it starts getting serious?

- It’s slow, but thinking back, Aziraphale can certainly say that their relationship took a turn when Crowley took off his glasses when they were alone together. He had done that before, sometimes when they were drinking, but now, as soon as he walked through the door, he set down his glasses on the kitchen table and didn’t put them on again until he left the house. It showed a vulnerability Aziraphale had never really noticed before. It as a small detail, that demonstrated just how much Crowley really trusted him now.)

17. When they find a time machine, where do they go?

- They visit old high cultures, places they never visited when they were still thriving, maybe even places they were barely aware of at the time. They spend a quite considerable time in south America in the ninth century, while Charlemagne reigns in drizzly central Europe. Crowley loves the rain forest, he loves the temperature, and even if it’s a bit warm for Aziraphale’s taste, it is all worth it, when he sees Crowley – in his serpent form – vanishing into the forest, only for him to later return, a wide grin on his face, hair dishevelled, twigs and leaves caught in it. It’s like a garden, only infinitely better. They trade for food with the people in the cities, but mostly keep to nature and to themselves. It is peaceful.

question: 28 for the ship HC one
answer:
28. Why do they get jealous?

- Aziraphale gets jealous when people hit on Crowley when he’s wearing incredibly tight jeans. It happens and he has to restrain himself not to miracle away their voice boxes. Crowley gets jealous when Aziraphale is too friendly. Sometimes, the angel is decidedly too angelic and Crowley literally senses people developing very intense crushes, very quickly. It’s just something about Aziraphale that seems to make him universally lovable (not that Crowley can blame them. He knows this best of all) but the angel is his now. He put in all the work (millennia of flirting, saving Aziraphale’s life countless times, even stopping time and saving the world) and he will see the rewards, as he wipes those people’s minds clean of their feelings perhaps accidentally even of any memory they had of a certain angel.

body:
Consider if you will…

Crowley is feeding (see: sinking) the ducks at St. James Park And next thing he knows the world is suddenly upside down and much wetter. He tries to get up out of the pond but something keeps pushing him back in. Not quite an invisible hand but more insistent than the slippery ground has any right to be.

Meanwhile about ten paces away Azirapahle is tearing up bread and avoiding his eyes as if to say “Don’t look at me. Someone’s throwing miracles around. Besides you can hardly say you didn’t have this coming. The poor ducks you’ve drowned over the centuries!” Aziraphale’s glances (or non glances as it were) were very vocal.

Crowley starts cursing up a blue streak at the angel, but there’s no real heat to his words and they both know it. But it’s so loud even the spies halt their clandestine meetings to stare at the mad man in the water.

Aziraphale starts to laugh, really laugh. Something that rarely happens sober. and Crowley pauses his rant to bask in the beautiful sound.

The sun is poking out from the clouds. It’s a beautiful day.

Besides you can hardly say you didn’t have this coming. The poor ducks you’ve drowned over the centuries!” Aziraphale’s glances (or non glances as it were) were very vocal.

Crowley starts cursing up a blue streak at the angel, but there’s no real heat to his words and they both know it. But it’s so loud even the spies halt their clandestine meetings to stare at the mad man in the water.

Aziraphale starts to laugh, really laugh. Something that rarely happens sober. and Crowley pauses his rant to bask in the beautiful sound.

The sun is poking out from the clouds. It’s a beautiful day.
